He wore a white tanktop and his leather pants. On his right shoulder, he bore the mark of the pack. Which was known widely throughout Greece as a Scynthian Warrior. On his other arm he bore a tiger and a wolf, with the names &quot;Xanthe&quot; and &quot;Jadeyn&quot; written below each animal. On his wrist in red ink, was the word &quot;Justice&quot; written out.<br>
<br>
In his arms he carried a large crate and glanced around as to where he would be taking it. Since Wulf left Scynthia by Amazon law, he lived in Athens and worked as a metal worker in designing new weapons and such. He was there to make a delivery to the army of Troy.<br>
